Event Handling & Processing (Short)

Definition: Event Handling allows the program to respond to user actions like button clicks. Event Processing is the logic executed after the event (e.g., validation, DB update, UI update).

Implementation in Project:

Event Sources: JButton – Create, Login, Deposit, Withdraw

Listener: ActionListener with lambda expressions

create.addActionListener(e -> createAccount());
deposit.addActionListener(e -> deposit());


Processing Steps:

Validate input

Execute business logic (deposit/withdraw with threads)

Update database via JDBC

Update GUI output

Advantages:

Responsive GUI

Secure input validation

Multithreading support

Real-time database updates

Rubric Mapping: Event Handling and Processing ✅ Fully Implemented
